            <para>
               <para.body>We have seen that diagonalizing a matrix helps us in determining the transformation properties of a given matrix. But there are other reasons why one might want to diagonalize a matrix <math>
                     <latex>\Mtrx{A}</latex>
                  </math>. For example, the task of computing a (high) power <math>
                     <latex>\Mtrx{A}^r</latex>
                  </math> can be quite labor intensive, especially if <math>
                     <latex>r</latex>
                  </math> is large. The following result tells us, however, that this task can be simplified hugely if <math>
                     <latex>\Mtrx{A}</latex>
                  </math> is diagonalizable.</para.body>
